Ferris Taylor https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ferris_Taylor 0 Ferris Taylor (March 25, 1888 – March 7, 1961) was an American film actor. He appeared in more than 120 films between 1933 and 1958. He also made guest appearances on The Cisco Kid starring Duncan Renaldo and Leo Carillo in the early 1950s. He was born in Henrietta, Texas, and died in Hollywood, California from a heart attack.
